    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1155: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"
                            >Garrett</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-22T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 22, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Please take occasion to deliver the following message from me to the Chief of
                    the Government: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I am asking our Ambassador to tell you how deeply I appreciate the
                            whole-hearted support Italy gave this afternoon at Geneva to the
                            President’s proposals and which was expressed with such eloquence and
                            conviction by Signor <persName corresp="#p_GD1">Grandi</persName>. May I
                            add a personal line of thanks to you and tell you what great pleasure it
                            gives me to see our two Governments working side by side toward a
                            successful solution of the problem of disarmament.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
